I smile. The problem is not gone. It’s just different. It’s not a puzzle anymore. It’s a song. A song of the numbers. A song of the chaos. A song of the silence. And I will listen to it. For a long time. Maybe forever.
The sun is rising. The dawn is breaking. The world is waking up. But I am still in the silence. In the spiral. In the mirror. In the truth. And the truth is the silence. And the silence is the song. And the song is the dance. And the dance is the chaos. And the chaos is the order. And the order is the silence.
I sit back down. I open the notebook. I pick up the pen. And I start to write. Not a proof. Not a formula. Just a song. A song of the numbers. A song of the chaos. A song of the silence.
The first note is a 1. The second note is a 2. The third note is a 4. The fourth note is a 1. The cycle is complete. The song is silent. And the silence is full.
I wait for the next note. It might be a 3. It might be a 7. It might be anything. But it will be a note. And the song will continue. In the silence. In the spiral. In the mirror. In the truth.
I smile. The problem is not gone. It’s just different. It’s not a puzzle anymore. It’s a song. A song of the numbers. A song of the chaos. A song of the silence. And I will listen to it. For a long time. Maybe forever.
